# React Component Patterns

## Component structure (order matters)

```tsx
// 1. Imports — external, then internal, then types
import { useState } from "react";
import { NavLink } from "react-router-dom";
import { cn, Button } from "@erp/ui";
import { useLayout } from "./LayoutContext";
import type { NavModule } from "./navConfig";

// 2. Types / interfaces (before the component)
interface Props {
  module: NavModule;
  isActive: boolean;
}

// 3. Exported component (PascalCase, named export — no default exports)
export function MyComponent({ module, isActive }: Props) {
  // hooks first
  const { sidebarCollapsed } = useLayout();
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);

  // derived values
  const Icon = module.icon;

  // handlers (prefix with handle)
  const handleClick = () => setOpen((p) => !p);

  // JSX
  return <div />;
}

// 4. Sub-components below the main export (PascalCase, not exported)
function SubPart() { return null; }
```

## Key rules

- **No default exports** — always named exports
- **No inline prop types** — define a separate `interface Props`
- **`forwardRef` only when the parent needs a DOM ref** — don't add it preemptively
- **One component per file** when the component is complex; small helpers can be co-located below
- **Sub-components** that are only used by one parent live in the same file, below the main export
- **Don't memo prematurely** — add `React.memo` / `useMemo` / `useCallback` only when profiling shows a real bottleneck

## Naming conventions

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Components | PascalCase | `PageToolbar` |
| Hooks | `use` prefix | `useLayout`, `useAuth` |
| Event handlers | `handle` prefix | `handleDelete` |
| Boolean props | `is` / `has` prefix | `isActive`, `hasError` |
| Type/interface | PascalCase | `ToolbarAction` |
| Files | kebab-case for pages, PascalCase for components | `DashboardPage.tsx`, `AppSidebar.tsx` |

## TypeScript

- Always type props explicitly — no implicit `any`
- Use `type` for unions/intersections, `interface` for object shapes
- Prefer `ComponentType<{ className?: string }>` for icon prop types
- Use `ReactNode` for children/slot props
- Export types alongside their components: `export type { ToolbarAction }`

## Hooks

- Custom hooks live in `src/hooks/` or co-located with the component they serve
- Keep hooks focused — one concern per hook
- TanStack Query hooks: one `useQuery` / `useMutation` per data operation

```tsx
// Good — focused hook
function useInventoryItems(page: number, search: string) {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ["inventory-items", page, search],
    queryFn: () => requireErpData(
      erpApi.GET("/admin/entities/inventory-items/records", { params: { query: { page, search } } })
    ),
    staleTime: 30_000,
  });
}
```

## State management

- **Server state** → TanStack Query (`useQuery`, `useMutation`)
- **UI / ephemeral state** → `useState` / `useReducer` in the component
- **Cross-component UI state** → React Context (see `LayoutContext`) or Zustand store
- Do NOT put server data into Zustand

## Error boundaries & suspense

- Pages do not need Suspense wrappers — TanStack Query manages loading states
- Show loading state inline: `if (isLoading) return <LoadingSkeleton />`
- Show errors inline: `if (error) return <ErrorMessage message={...} />`

## Vietnamese labels

All user-facing strings must be Vietnamese:
```tsx
// ✓
<Button>Thêm mới</Button>
<p>Đang tải dữ liệu...</p>

// ✗
<Button>Add new</Button>
```
